 {"id":"bd-878p","title":"Distributed lab testing: network simulation and fault injection","description":"# Distributed Lab Testing

## Goal

Extend the lab runtime to support deterministic testing of distributed systems with network simulation and fault injection.

## Background

Testing distributed systems is hard because:
- Real networks are non-deterministic
- Failures are hard to reproduce
- Multi-node setups are complex

The lab runtime solves this with simulation:
- Virtual network with controlled latency
- Deterministic message ordering
- Injectable faults (partitions, delays, losses)

## SimulatedNetwork

```rust
pub struct SimulatedNetwork {
    /// All nodes in the simulation
    nodes: HashMap<NodeId, SimulatedNode>,

    /// In-flight messages
    in_flight: BinaryHeap<ScheduledMessage>,

    /// Network conditions
    conditions: NetworkConditions,

    /// Random source (deterministic)
    rng: StdRng,

    /// Current logical time
    now: LogicalTime,
}

pub struct SimulatedNode {
    /// Node's inbox
    inbox: VecDeque<Message>,

    /// Whether node is partitioned
    partitioned: bool,

    /// Artificial latency to this node
    latency: Duration,
}

pub struct ScheduledMessage {
    /// When message arrives
    delivery_time: LogicalTime,

    /// Source node
    from: NodeId,

    /// Destination node
    to: NodeId,

    /// Message payload
    payload: Vec<u8>,
}
```

## NetworkConditions

```rust
pub struct NetworkConditions {
    /// Base latency for all messages
    base_latency: Duration,

    /// Latency jitter (±)
    jitter: Duration,

    /// Probability of message loss
    loss_rate: f64,

    /// Probability of message duplication
    duplicate_rate: f64,

    /// Probability of message reordering
    reorder_rate: f64,

    /// Bandwidth limit (bytes/sec, 0 = unlimited)
    bandwidth: u64,
}

impl NetworkConditions {
    pub fn perfect() -> Self { /* no failures */ }
    pub fn lossy() -> Self { /* 1% loss */ }
    pub fn slow() -> Self { /* high latency */ }
    pub fn chaos() -> Self { /* everything bad */ }
}
```

## Fault Injection

```rust
impl SimulatedNetwork {
    /// Partition a node from the network
    fn partition(&mut self, node: NodeId);

    /// Heal a partition
    fn heal(&mut self, node: NodeId);

    /// Create asymmetric partition (A can't reach B, but B can reach A)
    fn partition_asymmetric(&mut self, from: NodeId, to: NodeId);

    /// Delay all messages to a node
    fn add_latency(&mut self, node: NodeId, latency: Duration);

    /// Drop next N messages to a node
    fn drop_messages(&mut self, node: NodeId, count: usize);

    /// Pause a node (simulates GC pause or CPU stall)
    fn pause(&mut self, node: NodeId, duration: Duration);
}
```

## DistributedLabRuntime

```rust
pub struct DistributedLabRuntime {
    /// Individual node runtimes
    nodes: HashMap<NodeId, LabRuntime>,

    /// Simulated network
    network: SimulatedNetwork,

    /// Configuration
    config: DistributedLabConfig,
}

pub struct DistributedLabConfig {
    /// Number of nodes
    node_count: usize,

    /// Seed for determinism
    seed: u64,

    /// Network conditions
    network: NetworkConditions,

    /// Whether to capture traces
    capture_trace: bool,
}

impl DistributedLabRuntime {
    /// Advance simulation until all nodes quiescent
    fn run_until_quiescent(&mut self);

    /// Advance simulation by one step
    fn step(&mut self) -> StepResult;

    /// Get node runtime for spawning tasks
    fn node(&mut self, id: NodeId) -> &mut LabRuntime;

    /// Inject network fault
    fn inject_fault(&mut self, fault: NetworkFault);
}
```

## Determinism

The simulation is fully deterministic:
1. Same seed → same RNG
2. Message delivery order: deterministic priority queue
3. Faults injected at predetermined times
4. No wall-clock dependencies

## Trace Capture

Distributed traces capture:
- Message send/receive events
- Logical clock values
- Fault injection events
- Node state transitions

```rust
pub enum DistributedTraceEvent {
    MessageSent { from: NodeId, to: NodeId, at: LogicalTime },
    MessageDelivered { from: NodeId, to: NodeId, at: LogicalTime },
    MessageDropped { from: NodeId, to: NodeId, reason: DropReason },
    NodePartitioned { node: NodeId },
    NodeHealed { node: NodeId },
    NodePaused { node: NodeId, duration: Duration },
}
```

## Test Patterns

### Partition Tolerance Test
```rust
#[test]
fn test_survives_partition() {
    let mut lab = DistributedLabRuntime::new(config);

    // Set up distributed state
    lab.node(node_a).spawn(writer_task);
    lab.node(node_b).spawn(reader_task);

    // Run until stable
    lab.run_until_quiescent();

    // Partition node B
    lab.inject_fault(NetworkFault::Partition(node_b));

    // Continue operation on A
    lab.node(node_a).spawn(write_more);
    lab.run_until_quiescent();

    // Heal partition
    lab.inject_fault(NetworkFault::Heal(node_b));

    // Verify B catches up
    lab.run_until_quiescent();
    assert!(lab.node(node_b).query(state_matches_a));
}
```

### Message Loss Test
```rust
#[test]
fn test_retries_on_loss() {
    let mut lab = DistributedLabRuntime::new(
        config.with_network(NetworkConditions::lossy())
    );

    // Operation should succeed despite losses
    let result = lab.run_distributed_operation();
    assert!(result.is_ok());
}
```

